[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating compilation issues**\n\nI'm considering why the test might have failed to compile, potentially due to a direct import of `java.security.spec.ECGenParameterSpec`. I’m confirming that ECGenParameterSpec indeed falls under `java.security.spec`. So, could the compilation failure be related to `ProvECPrivateKeyTest` using a record that requires Java 16? It seems plausible that this could be the problem, and I need to look into it further to resolve the issue.\n\n**Investigating serialization issues**\n\nI'm considering using a different constructor while keeping the same hook. I'll add a simple test called `keyPairGeneratorSerializationRoundTrip` to ensure it executes the same call sites. However, if there's an issue with a private method not being triggered, I might be in trouble. It could be that standard serialization doesn't work because `ProvECPrivateKey` has a `writeReplace` method it's inheriting. I’ll need to look into that further!", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0714d99c945a354c016a3fa002fb2c8190a1be740808a8cb69\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqP6AZb5V7jbydj-m7UaDv05gtwematv8OXbrsLSXlnr0IXM4TJujix-1ue0WxjIYipqkw1oaK3F_JLebKXPmGmO0zGCezkVix_Q5Y_IaLQVV2i6vAaXiZJA68rCjsTe1TBgEvlPIzqDFyX-1S7MlIXuOsp6OC0utyx65k15AmlmcMTH-lcHQb7ksCbDG92fHG4yguxHpMu-O0SJRYbPJnkqkI7UCK6eA_Xhw5fLPbFtL5D1jQaMrm4rIEmzoblojDY826puHOHJA_SY0BpSMABgi8whReEfbu26eFlUoTSmGWxGNAHkZ2AwkTUsCOkzzXA0DD_EjT5Iw1N463zXeoUkW3OECKfYV3jVDXgbtfcl5kuoh-xDIFc_Ba3tp9xJ3ZsQnPZBRaaBuCI941uqlChNaOuLjs4N_DNt9WhAzB4nq0HhMrrjVKZSuhLFlNwxc-q8a-ZPAxkpGloHJNtvzEMbxApfxfz6dtkVmbdPROm0fzzaTTbIHEIoRD4wFBa-S075J436V0CgpAtKMOdk3lqIoapAjUqSaIP7PF7WvVlcos-bJQffEp1rJpbbvg3_n2AhsKl1A8FrD7xQ82DPXGazG406IyM3I7a8HPqxYNcM-ya_p0MP1tgdXAWmg49d2yJ28DuRCBXdZ5SRIUHyzrdxs0-2H2Kz9E3pP_5807lrtPx2FmHjY6Y8Z47ILuFKDEIdy6HSyXetXVr8FQ3xwhdxlribBJVvLDwA-P4LiOkI_M11ajvRt4DFX3hURHret